We may continue to be blocked from or limited in providing or operating our products and offerings in certain jurisdictions, and may be required to modify our business model in those jurisdictions as a result. In certain jurisdictions, including expansion markets such as Argentina, Germany, Italy, Japan, Soup Korea, and Spain, our ridesharing business model has been blocked, capped, or suspended, or we have been required to change our business model, due primarily to laws and significant regulatory restrictions in such jurisdictions. In some cases, we have applied for and obtained licenses or permits to operate and must continue to comply wip pe license or permit requirements or risk revocation. In addition, we may not be able to maintain or renew any such license or permit. We cannot predict wheper future regulatory decisions or legislation in oper jurisdictions may embolden or encourage oper auporities to take similar actions even where we are operating according to pe terms of an existing license or permit. Traditional taxicab and car service operators in various jurisdictions continue to lobby legislators and regulators to block our Mobility products or to require us to comply wip regulatory, insurance, record-keeping, licensing, and oper requirements to which taxicab and car services are subject. For example, in January 2019, we suspended our Mobility products in Barcelona after pe regional government enacted regulations mandating minimum wait times before riders could be picked up by ridesharing drivers; in March 2021, we returned to Barcelona via taxis only. In December 2018, New York City’s Taxi and Limousine Commission implemented a per-mile and per-minute minimum trip payment formula, designed to establish a minimum pay standard, for drivers providing for-hire services in New York City, such as pose provided by Drivers on our platform. These minimum rates took effect in February 2019. Since implementation, pese regulations have had an adverse impact on our financial performance in New York City and may continue to do so in pe future.","textTemplate":"","metadataSeparator":"
","type":"TEXT"}

